Title:   Decomposing Learning by Doing in New Plants. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 561-83
Issue: 4
Volume: 101
Year: 1993
Month:  August 
Abstract:
  This paper examines learning by doing in the context of a production
 function in which the other arguments are labor, human capital, physical
 capital, and vintage as a proxy for embodied technical change in physical
 capital. Learning is further decomposed into organization learning,
 capital learning, and manual task learning. The model is tested with
 time-series and cross-section data for various samples of up to 2,150
 plants over a fourteen-year period.  Copyright 1993 by University of Chicago Press.
